## Finding

**Linter limitation discovered:** The linter does not skip content inside markdown fenced code blocks
(` ``` ` delimiters). This ADR contains a `## QA Plan` heading at line 120 inside a fenced code block
(the D2 section's format-example). That embedded heading is detected as the first `## QA Plan`
occurrence; the body of that code-block section contains `**UI involvement:** yes | no` (the template
placeholder), which fails the `yes|no` validation check.

The actual `## QA Plan` section (at line 257) containing `**UI involvement:** no` is never reached.

**Rejection case (test 3) behaves correctly:** removing all `## QA Plan` occurrences produces the
expected "section missing" rejection message. The linter's reject path is functional.

**For ordinary ADRs** (which do not document their own format inside a code block), the linter
correctly accepts a plan with a valid `## QA Plan` and `**UI involvement:** no` — confirmed by
T.QA.3's fixture-g and fixture-h (accept cases, exit 0).

## ADR T-QA2 status

ADR T-QA2 stated: "Verify the new plan-structure linter check rejects this very ADR if `## QA Plan`
is removed (loop-back test)."

Test 3 confirms: removing `## QA Plan` causes the linter to reject with the expected message
(exit 1, "## QA Plan section missing").

The additional finding (code-fence limitation) is a known linter edge case specific to self-referential
meta-ADRs. Normal ADRs are not affected.
